LEVEL: CERTIFIED GOLDEN
FILE: /standards/ISO_WD_24942_Machine_Vision.sci

WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified reference for ISO/DIS 24942 (under development), which
standardises the specification parameters for cameras and image sensors
used in machine vision.

WHY IT EXISTS
Machine vision cameras (global shutter, high frame rate, NIR sensitivity)
are increasingly used for VFX witness cameras and photogrammetry. GIOP
must reference this standard to ensure that data ingested from such
cameras carries the correct sensor geometry and noise characteristics.

HOW IT WORKS
The standard defines reporting of: sensor resolution, pixel size,
quantum efficiency curve, read noise, saturation capacity, spectral
sensitivity, and opto‑mechanical interface. GIOP uses this metadata
to build an IDT for machine vision cameras.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Photogrammetry and 3D scan pipelines.
- On‑set witness camera arrays for virtual production.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers ingesting machine vision data into GIOP.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Standardises the characterisation of machine vision sensors so that
GIOP can automatically linearise them without custom calibration.

